         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Hybrid Cloud enabling infrastructure and services</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>T018/18</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="48000000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>This Prior Information Notice (PIN) is to announce that the Malta Information Technology Agency (MITA) will be publishing a Call for Tender (CfT) for the procurement of a hybrid cloud enabling infrastructure and services in approximately March of 2018.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="MT"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Malta.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>MITA will be seeking the implementation, support and operation of a hybrid cloud enabling infrastructure and services.</P>
                  <P>The hybrid cloud will be used for production and non-production environments for the Government of Malta, enabling it to support the achievement of the Digital Malta Strategy. The Solution is to be made up of the following service dimensions:</P>
                  <P>— hyper-converged infrastructure and Infrastructure-as-a-Service,</P>
                  <P>— software services, management and DevOps,</P>
                  <P>— operational and support services, security and controls, and billing and usage metering.</P>
                  <P>The on-premise part of the hybrid cloud will be based on a hyper-converged stack (potentially spread across 2 geographically dispersed sites) and will include compute and store elements of a sizeable order (e.g. 500+ cores, 10TB RAM and 500TB storage), with the ability to scale when required.</P>
                  <P>The document available to download from the URL: https://procurement.mita.gov.mt depicts the main services that will be required to make up the hybrid cloud, which are, but not limited to the following:</P>
                  <P>1. On-premise based services:</P>
                  <P>— hyper-converged infrastructure and software fabric,</P>
                  <P>— infrastructure as a Service,</P>
                  <P>— storage as a Service,</P>
                  <P>— applications Platform as a Service (Paas),</P>
                  <P>— database as a Service.</P>
                  <P>2. public Cloud based services:</P>
                  <P>— identity aggregation and federation as a service,</P>
                  <P>— integration platform as a service,</P>
                  <P>— API management as a service,</P>
                  <P>— Blockchain as a service,</P>
                  <P>— mobile Backend as a service.</P>
                  <P>The relevant elements making up the solution will need to be costed as part of the infrastructure and subscription cost.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>More information about MITA, and on how to participate to the agency's procurement activities is available from the URL: https://procurement.mita.gov.mt</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
